    <section>
        <div class="container-narrow">
            <h2>The Problem Most Businesses Don't Know They Have</h2>
            
            <div class="problem-narrative">
                <p>A customer fills out your contact form.<br>
                They click submit.<br>
                Your system shows "Thank you."</p>

                <p class="highlight">But the lead never reaches your CRM.</p>

                <p>No error message. No alert. No record it ever happened.</p>

                <p>Your team assumes everything works because you tested it once. Your sales rep never follows up because they never saw the lead. The customer moves on to a competitor.</p>

                <p class="highlight">You never knew what you lost.</p>
            </div>

            <p>This isn't hypothetical. It's happening right now in businesses running on:</p>
            
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Zapier or Make.com integrations that silently time out</li>
                <li>CRM APIs that reject leads without logging why</li>
                <li>OAuth tokens that expire mid-week</li>
                <li>Rate limits that cause 30-minute delays during high traffic</li>
            </ul>

            <p>The technical systems you depend on fail more often than you think. And when they do, they fail silently.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="alt-bg">
        <div class="container-narrow">
            <h2>How Leads Fail (And Why You Don't Know)</h2>

            <div class="failure-grid">
                <div class="failure-card">
                    <h4>Webhook Timeout</h4>
                    <p>Your form sends data to Make.com or Zapier, but the request takes 31 seconds. The webhook times out. The lead is gone.</p>
                    <p class="impact">Business impact: Lost sale. No record. No retry.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="failure-card">
                    <h4>CRM Validation Rejection</h4>
                    <p>Your CRM requires a phone number in a specific format. The lead submitted a valid number, but in the wrong format. HubSpot or Salesforce rejects it.</p>
                    <p class="impact">Business impact: Lead dropped. No one is notified. Form appears to work.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="failure-card">
                    <h4>Auth Token Expiration</h4>
                    <p>Your Google Sheets or CRM integration loses authentication at 2 AM on a Tuesday. Every lead submitted after that moment fails.</p>
                    <p class="impact">Business impact: Hours or days of silent failures before anyone notices.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="failure-card">
                    <h4>Rate Limiting</h4>
                    <p>Your integration hits the CRM's API rate limit during a traffic spike. Requests queue up, then fail.</p>
                    <p class="impact">Business impact: Leads delayed by 20+ minutes or dropped entirely.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="failure-card">
                    <h4>Routing Collisions</h4>
                    <p>Two leads submit within seconds. Your system assigns both to the same rep. The second lead is never followed up.</p>
                    <p class="impact">Business impact: Duplicate assignment or complete drop depending on your setup.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <p style="margin-top: 48px; font-size: 19px; text-align: center;" class="highlight">
                None of these trigger alerts in standard setups. None show up in your CRM. None get retried.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

